==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crocein
<hw>Cro"ce*in</hw> <pr>(kr?"s?-?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Croceous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A name given to any
one of several yellow or scarlet dyestuffs of artificial production and
complex structure. In general they are diazo and sulphonic acid
derivatives of benzene and naphthol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Croceous</ent>⟦br⟧
